    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="333"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.248/125</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-14">July 14,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>: Co<note n="18" xml:id="d333fn18">Division
                        of Controls.</note> has interpreted your attached memorandum of a
                    conversation with the British Ambassador on July 8<note n="19" xml:id="d333fn19">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> regarding the granting of further
                    export licenses for the shipment from the United States of aircraft to Iran as
                    an instruction to terminate forthwith all such further shipments, and oral
                    instructions have already been given to revoke certain licenses issued to the
                    Curtiss-Wright Corporation authorizing the export of aircraft parts to Iran.</p>
                <p>Would you please let me know whether you intended that such drastic action,
                    including a ban on the exportation of aircraft parts, should be taken without
                    further investigation of the situation existing at present in Iran.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d333fn20">Marginal note: “You may wish to explore this with the
                        British Embassy—SW”.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
